						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar, left of the entrance to the Trimūrti temple (below No. 56: A.R. 87 of 1953-1954.)</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1053, Mahādvādaśī, corresponding to 1131 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of a perpetual lamp (to god Vishṇu) by a son (name not clear) of Sōmaya of Śāṇḍilya-<hi rend="italic">gōtra,</hi> and his wife.</p>						

